@inherits ComponentBase

@* THE EXPLICIT DEFAULT BASE (decision 173, register C4). Writing `@inherits ComponentBase` -- the
   framework base every component already has -- changes nothing: Razor's own codegen emits the same
   `: ComponentBase` it emits with no directive at all. So there is nothing to merge and nothing to
   refuse. Before decision 173 the unqualified spelling fell into sibling resolution and was refused
   ([unsupported-directive] "resolves to ComponentBase.razor, which does not exist") while the fully-
   qualified spelling was already admitted. Now the bare name is the default too -- a no-op, byte-
   identical to PlainCounter which writes no @inherits. (A sibling ComponentBase.razor legally shadows
   the framework base; that case lives in Supported/InheritShadow and still MERGES, because the default
   fallback fires only after the sibling check fails.) *@

<div id="wrap"><span id="out">@currentCount</span><button id="inc" @onclick="Increment">inc</button></div>

@code {
    int currentCount = 5;
    void Increment() { currentCount++; }
}
